In England, in the seven days to 12 March, there were 349,029 new confirmed cases (617.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 March, there were 209,540 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 67% (139,489 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 17 March is 16,860,551 (29,815.2 cases per 100,000 population).
